The paper deals with image processing and feature extraction using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The focus is on identifying handwritten scripts, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of deep learning techniques for feature extraction and classification is a key aspect of the paper, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG). Information retrieval (cs.IR) is also relevant as the paper deals with identifying specific words within scripts. Finally, artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is a broad category that encompasses all of the above topics and is therefore a likely sub-category.
